def load_images_from_folder(folder):
    images = []
    for filename in os.listdir(folder):
        img = cv2.imread(os.path.join(folder,filename))
        if img is not None:
            images.append(img)
        if len(images)>15:
            break
    fig=plt.figure(figsize=(10,12))
    plt.title(folder, y=1.02)
    plt.axis('off')
    xrange=range(1,17)
    
    for img,x in zip(images,xrange):
        ax=fig.add_subplot(4,4,x)
        ax.imshow(img)
        ax.set_title(img.shape)

def crop_images_from_folder(folder, outdir):
    images = []
    crops = []
    #load images
    for filename in os.listdir(folder): 
        img = cv2.imread(os.path.join(folder, filename))
        if img is not None:
            images.append(img)
#         if len(images)>7:
#             break
    # plot 8 samples of all the images
    fig=plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
    plt.title(folder, y=1.02)
    plt.axis('off')
    xrange=range(1,9)
    for img,x in zip(images,xrange):
        ax=fig.add_subplot(2,4,x)
        ax.imshow(img)
        ax.set_title(img.shape)
        
    # crop images  
    os.chdir(outdir) # change current directory
    for img,filename in zip(images,os.listdir('../../{}'.format(folder))):
        height, width, channels = img.shape
        h1=height//8
        h2=7*height//8
        w1=width//8
        w2=7*width//8
        crop=img[h1:h2, w1:w2]
        crops.append(crop)
        cv2.imwrite("{}.jpg".format(filename), crop)
            
    # plot some samples of cropped images    
    fig=plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
    plt.title("cropped {}".format(folder), y=1.02)
    plt.axis('off')
    xrange=range(1,9)
    for cropped,x in zip(crops,xrange):
        ax=fig.add_subplot(2,4,x)
        ax.imshow(cropped)
        ax.set_title(cropped.shape)
    os.chdir('../../../code') # change back directory
